        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 1:58PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 158 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bogus Basin Ski Area, or 13 miles north of Boise, moving northeast at
15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust reducing
visibilities. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Bogus Basin Ski Area around 210 PM MDT.
Harris Creek Summit around 230 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
